body:
And if the name are similar enough, do you just not allow the creation of the guild? I don't think that's a good idea because of things like guild squatting and power-abusing mods. For example, someone took over +WhiteVictimsofBlackCrime and repurposed it, and those who wanted to see "white victims of black crime" had to move to +WhiteVictimsofBlackCrimes. Sure, you could've come up with a more different name, but I don't think that should be necessary.

The real problem here is that the "l" and "I" are the same, or almost the same, in the font that's being used.

![](https://i.ibb.co/MR5FfzB/sfrohne.png)
body_html:
